  "description": "Positive known-answer vectors for the rfc9162-sha256 list commitment (RFC 9162 §2.1.1): leaf hash = SHA-256(0x00 || d), internal node = SHA-256(0x01 || left || right), split k = largest power of two strictly less than n. Each leaf d is a 32-byte digest; the leaf set is off-chain and the only on-wire artefact is the 32-byte root. Empty trees (n == 0) are forbidden. The six tree sizes 1,2,3,4,5,7 exercise the balanced cases plus the odd-leaf recursion edges (split 3 -> 2+1, 5 -> 4+1, 7 -> 4+3). Every root MUST be byte-identical across conforming implementations.",
